WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.350 --> 00:00:04.496
NULL:  Every gap, every shortcut, every forgotten door -

2
00:00:04.496 --> 00:00:05.765
I will find it.

3
00:00:06.065 --> 00:00:08.956
VEGA:  Not tonight. One stolen login should never be

4
00:00:08.956 --> 00:00:10.305
enough to end a city.

5
00:00:10.605 --> 00:00:12.427
NOVA:  So where do we begin?

6
00:00:12.727 --> 00:00:14.967
VEGA:  Where every attacker does - at the wall.

7
00:00:16.017 --> 00:00:19.455
NULL:  Every fortress has a door. I only need

8
00:00:19.455 --> 00:00:22.712
one careless soul to leave one open.

9
00:00:23.012 --> 00:00:25.584
VEGA:  Then meet the three guardians of the gate.

10
00:00:25.584 --> 00:00:27.972
I'm Vega. This is the apprentice, Nova.

11
00:00:28.272 --> 00:00:31.574
NOVA:  Let's walk the walls.

12
00:00:32.624 --> 00:00:35.074
VEGA:  Layer one is the perimeter, who gets in,

13
00:00:35.074 --> 00:00:36.544
and what they may touch.

14
00:00:36.844 --> 00:00:41.414
Three families stand the wall: Access Control, Identification,

15
00:00:41.414 --> 00:00:42.372
and Physical.

16
00:00:43.422 --> 00:00:46.907
VEGA:  Three districts light up the map: AC, IA,

17
00:00:46.907 --> 00:00:47.502
and PE.

18
00:00:47.802 --> 00:00:49.904
NOVA:  The gatekeepers of the city.

19
00:00:50.954 --> 00:00:53.554
VEGA:  First, the Gatekeeper, Access Control.

20
00:00:53.854 --> 00:00:56.654
VEGA:  It decides who may enter, and exactly what

21
00:00:56.654 --> 00:00:57.654
they may touch.

22
00:00:57.954 --> 00:01:00.745
VEGA:  In the real world, that's the policies and

23
00:01:00.745 --> 00:01:04.266
mechanisms deciding which users and processes may use

24
00:01:04.266 --> 00:01:05.794
which systems and data.

25
00:01:06.844 --> 00:01:08.826
NOVA:  Where does access begin?

26
00:01:09.126 --> 00:01:12.928
VEGA:  With accounts. AC-2 governs every account from birth

27
00:01:12.928 --> 00:01:13.806
to deletion.

28
00:01:14.856 --> 00:01:17.805
VEGA:  Then the rule that saves you again and

29
00:01:17.805 --> 00:01:20.056
again, AC-6, Least Privilege.

30
00:01:20.356 --> 00:01:22.263
NULL:  Less for them to give me when I

31
00:01:22.263 --> 00:01:23.371
take an account...

32
00:01:24.421 --> 00:01:28.136
ARCHIVIST:  Employ the principle of least privilege, allowing only

33
00:01:28.136 --> 00:01:31.782
authorized accesses for users (or processes acting on

34
00:01:31.782 --> 00:01:35.153
behalf of users) that are necessary to accomplish

35
00:01:35.153 --> 00:01:37.217
assigned organizational tasks.

36
00:01:38.267 --> 00:01:41.037
VEGA:  Every request runs the same path: a policy

37
00:01:41.037 --> 00:01:43.147
decides, and a gate enforces it.

38
00:01:43.447 --> 00:01:45.911
VEGA:  Say Alice works in payroll. Policy lets her

39
00:01:45.911 --> 00:01:48.547
open payroll records; the same gate blocks Bob

40
00:01:48.547 --> 00:01:49.407
from marketing.

41
00:01:49.707 --> 00:01:53.769
NOVA:  Decide, then enforce. AC-3 is the enforcement.

42
00:01:54.819 --> 00:01:56.819
VEGA:  Lock these three into memory.

43
00:02:03.419 --> 00:02:05.942
VEGA:  Say the Gatekeeper's oath with me. None pass

44
00:02:05.942 --> 00:02:08.179
unknown; none hold more than they need.

45
00:02:09.229 --> 00:02:13.189
VEGA:  Next, the Seal-Bearer, Identification and Authentication.

46
00:02:13.489 --> 00:02:17.058
NOVA:  Access Control trusts a name. This guardian proves

47
00:02:17.058 --> 00:02:18.271
the name is real.

48
00:02:19.321 --> 00:02:23.464
VEGA:  IA-2 demands proof of identity for every organizational

49
00:02:23.464 --> 00:02:23.841
user.

50
00:02:24.141 --> 00:02:27.984
VEGA:  Its enhancements - like IA-2(1) and IA-2(2) -

51
00:02:27.984 --> 00:02:31.741
are where multi-factor authentication lives.

52
00:02:32.791 --> 00:02:36.493
NOVA:  Multi-factor authentication - what is that, exactly?

53
00:02:36.793 --> 00:02:38.878
VEGA:  Two kinds of proof instead of one. It's

54
00:02:38.878 --> 00:02:41.231
why the pipeline breach we opened with would

55
00:02:41.231 --> 00:02:41.873
have failed.

56
00:02:42.923 --> 00:02:45.225
NOVA:  And the passwords and tokens themselves?

57
00:02:45.525 --> 00:02:49.525
VEGA:  IA-5 manages them, strength, rotation, protection.

58
00:02:50.575 --> 00:02:55.160
ARCHIVIST:  Uniquely identify and authenticate organizational users and associate

59
00:02:55.160 --> 00:02:59.014
that unique identification with processes acting on behalf

60
00:02:59.014 --> 00:03:00.011
of those users.

61
00:03:01.061 --> 00:03:03.261
VEGA:  Identity first. Always.

62
00:03:09.661 --> 00:03:12.777
VEGA:  The Seal-Bearer's oath. Prove the name, or the

63
00:03:12.777 --> 00:03:13.861
gate stays shut.

64
00:03:14.911 --> 00:03:17.548
VEGA:  Last on the wall, the Wall-Warden, Physical and

65
00:03:17.548 --> 00:03:18.951
Environmental Protection.

66
00:03:19.251 --> 00:03:21.609
NULL:  Why pick a lock... when I can walk

67
00:03:21.609 --> 00:03:23.066
through an open door?

68
00:03:23.366 --> 00:03:26.927
VEGA:  In reality, PE is physical access control -

69
00:03:26.927 --> 00:03:31.233
guards, badges, locks - plus protection from hazards

70
00:03:31.233 --> 00:03:33.966
like fire, power loss, and water.

71
00:03:35.016 --> 00:03:38.856
VEGA:  PE-3 enforces physical access at the doors themselves.

72
00:03:39.156 --> 00:03:42.654
NOVA:  Tailgating, propped doors, lost badges, this is where

73
00:03:42.654 --> 00:03:43.578
you stop them.

74
00:03:44.628 --> 00:03:47.464
VEGA:  And PE-6 watches and logs who comes and

75
00:03:47.464 --> 00:03:47.828
goes.

76
00:03:51.128 --> 00:03:56.188
ARCHIVIST:  Enforce physical access authorizations at [entry and exit

77
00:03:56.188 --> 00:03:57.164
points] by:

78
00:03:58.214 --> 00:04:00.694
VEGA:  Physical security is security.

79
00:04:06.814 --> 00:04:09.315
VEGA:  And the Wall-Warden's oath. A door is a

80
00:04:09.315 --> 00:04:10.854
decision - and I decide.

81
00:04:11.904 --> 00:04:14.222
VEGA:  Remember the framework? The wall is where you

82
00:04:14.222 --> 00:04:15.664
implement what you selected.

83
00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:19.186
NOVA:  Select from the baseline, implement here, assess later.

84
00:04:20.504 --> 00:04:24.472
NOVA:  Guardian check. Who proves your identity? Pause, and

85
00:04:24.472 --> 00:04:25.006
answer.

86
00:04:25.306 --> 00:04:28.627
Which guardian proves you are who you claim,

87
00:04:28.627 --> 00:04:29.834
before you pass?

88
00:04:30.134 --> 00:04:33.967
Your options. A. AC - Access Control. B.

89
00:04:33.967 --> 00:04:38.280
IA - Identification & Authentication. C. PE -

90
00:04:38.280 --> 00:04:39.142
Physical.

91
00:04:39.442 --> 00:04:42.344
NOVA:  Pause here and lock in your answer.

92
00:04:49.394 --> 00:04:52.171
VEGA:  The answer is B. IA - Identification &

93
00:04:52.171 --> 00:04:57.140
Authentication. Identification and Authentication proves who you are

94
00:04:57.140 --> 00:04:58.674
before you're let in.

95
00:04:59.724 --> 00:05:02.244
VEGA:  And the rule that limits the blast radius?

96
00:05:02.544 --> 00:05:05.496
'Only the access you truly need' is which

97
00:05:05.496 --> 00:05:06.072
control?

98
00:05:06.372 --> 00:05:11.444
Your options. A. AC-2 Account Management. B. AC-6

99
00:05:11.444 --> 00:05:16.620
Least Privilege. C. IA-5 Authenticator Management.

100
00:05:16.920 --> 00:05:19.822
NOVA:  Pause here and lock in your answer.

101
00:05:26.872 --> 00:05:30.288
VEGA:  The answer is B. AC-6 Least Privilege. AC-6,

102
00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:34.402
Least Privilege, grants only the access someone truly

103
00:05:34.402 --> 00:05:36.032
needs - nothing more.

104
00:05:37.082 --> 00:05:41.117
NOVA:  Scenario: someone tailgates into the server room. Whose

105
00:05:41.117 --> 00:05:42.144
watch is that?

106
00:05:42.444 --> 00:05:45.534
An intruder tailgates through a propped door into

107
00:05:45.534 --> 00:05:48.372
the server room. Which family should stop it?

108
00:05:48.672 --> 00:05:52.675
Your options. A. PE - Physical. B. AU

109
00:05:52.675 --> 00:05:55.920
- Audit. C. SR - Supply Chain.

110
00:05:56.220 --> 00:05:59.122
NOVA:  Pause here and lock in your answer.

111
00:06:06.172 --> 00:06:08.738
VEGA:  The answer is A. PE - Physical. Physical

112
00:06:08.738 --> 00:06:12.523
and Environmental Protection stops tailgating into the room

113
00:06:12.523 --> 00:06:12.972
itself.

114
00:06:14.022 --> 00:06:18.315
NOVA:  Notebook: the wall is access, identity, and physical

115
00:06:18.315 --> 00:06:19.884
- working together.

116
00:06:20.184 --> 00:06:23.344
VEGA:  Three guardians, one wall. The perimeter holds.

117
00:06:23.644 --> 00:06:27.459
NULL:  Fine. I'll stop knocking... and start hiding.

118
00:06:27.759 --> 00:06:30.559
VEGA:  Then we'll need the watchtowers. Next time.
